data.description: Welcome to the most extraordinary mid-century modern home located in the highly sought-after Fox Farm neighborhood. This unique property offers a blend of architectural brilliance and natural beauty, that shows true pride of ownership- you wont find another home like this one! What sets this home apart is its historical significance. Designed by the renowned architect George H Shanley, known for his iconic creations such as the Civic Center, Rainbow Hotel, and the Historic 10th Street bridge, this property is an architectural masterpiece. Owning this home means owning a piece of Great Falls' rich history. Step inside and be taken back in time with picturesque high windows for incredible natural light, tongue and groove ceilings, floating stairwell, large overhangs and brick accents throughout. Five bedrooms, three remodeled bathrooms and each room being thoughtfully designed to maximize comfort and functionality. The two beautiful fireplaces in this home serve as stunning accent pieces, adding warmth and elegance to the living areas. Whether you're entertaining guests or enjoying a cozy evening, these fireplaces create a truly enchanting atmosphere. The kitchen has been beautifully updated, featuring new cabinets, quartz countertops and top-of-the-line appliances including dual-fuel gas oven range that blends seamlessly with the homes overall design. Find peace and tranquility in the private backyard with concrete patio and serene landscaping, ready for easy indoor-outdoor entertainment. This one-of-a-kind home is a rare find with unparalleled charm, and you won't want to miss the opportunity to see it for yourself! Call Dustin Young 406-868-0736 or your real estate professional today to schedule your showing.
